The paper deals with efficient algorithms for estimating summary statistics of data streams, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of compressed counting and random projections also suggests a connection to machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The application of the algorithm to Web crawl data suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and possibly social networks (cs.SI).
